The `util` module provides `inspect()` for better object formatting:
```javascript
const util = require('util');
console.log(util.inspect(myObject, { showHidden: false, depth: null, colors: true }));
```

`util.debuglog()` can create conditional debug logs:
```javascript
const debuglog = util.debuglog('app');
debuglog('This only prints if NODE_DEBUG=app');
```
Run with `NODE_DEBUG=app node script.js`.
